I woke up very late today (like 14h). I guess I needed some sleep after my crazy
train ordeal yesterday. It was kinda sleeting anyway, so I didn't feel that bad
about missing out on the morning.

I was hungry, so I started walking to find somewhere to eat. I ran across a
restaurant that looked like it served local fare, and I got their beef goulash.
I ordered with "dumplings" which were the bread slices. I think I should have
tried with the wild rice instead.

